{D05: Colle System with ...e6} 1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 c5 3. e3 Nf6 4. c3 Nc6 5. Bd3 e6
6. O-O b6 (6... Qc7 7. Nbd2 Be7 8. dxc5 Bxc5 9. Qe2 Ne5 10. Nxe5 Qxe5 11. e4
Qh5 12. Bb5+ Kf8 13. Qxh5 Nxh5 14. Nb3 Bd6 15. Rd1 Nf6 16. exd5 exd5 17. Bg5
Ne4 18. Be3 Be6 19. f3 Nf6 20. Nd4 a6 21. Ba4 {Gausel,E (2540)-Wedberg,T (2475)
Munkebo 1998 1/2-1/2 (87)}) 7. Qe2 Be7 8. Nbd2 Bb7 9. b3 $146 (9. Rd1 O-O 10.
a3 Rc8 11. b4 cxb4 12. cxb4 a5 13. b5 Nb8 14. Bb2 Ne4 15. Rac1 Qd6 16. Bb1 Nd7
17. Nxe4 dxe4 18. Nd2 f5 19. Nc4 Qb8 20. Rc3 Bd5 21. Rdc1 Rcd8 22. f3 exf3 23.
gxf3 Bf6 {Buchnicek,P (2322)-Repkova,E (2391) Slovakia 2008 1-0 (42)}) 9... O-O
10. Bb2 cxd4 11. exd4 Rc8 12. Rae1 Qc7 13. Ne5 h6 (13... Nxe5 14. dxe5 (14.
Qxe5 $143 Bd6 15. Qe2 Bxh2+ 16. Kh1 Bd6 $17) 14... Nd7 15. b4 $11) 14. f4 $14
Bd6 15. Rf3 Nd7 16. Ref1 Ne7 ({Weaker is} 16... Ndxe5 17. fxe5 (17. dxe5 $6
Bc5+ 18. Kh1 Kh8 $14) 17... Be7 18. Rg3 $18) 17. Rh3 f5 {Black has a new
backward pawn: e6} 18. Ndf3 (18. Bb5 Nf6 $14) 18... Nf6 $11 19. Nh4 {White has
an active position} Ne4 {Black threatens to win material: Ne4xc3} 20. Bb1 Rf6
21. Kh1 Nxc3 $4 {there were better ways to keep up the pressure.} (21... Rff8
$142 $11 {the rescuing straw}) 22. Rxc3 $18 Qd8 23. Rxc8 Qxc8 24. Rc1 Qe8 25.
Bd3 Qd8 26. Nhf3 Qe8 (26... Ng6 {cannot change what is in store for White} 27.
g3 $18) 27. Bb5 Qh5 28. Ng1 (28. Nd7 $142 {finishes off the opponent} Rg6 29.
Nfe5 Qxe2 30. Bxe2 Rf6 $18) 28... Qxe2 29. Nxe2 g5 (29... Rf8 {is no salvation}
30. Bd7 Rf6 31. Kg1 $18) 30. g3 (30. Bd7 {keeps an even firmer grip} Ba6 31.
Ng3 Kh7 $18) 30... Kg7 31. a4 (31. h4 {and White can already relax} gxh4 32.
gxh4 Rf8 $18) 31... g4 (31... Rf8 {doesn't get the cat off the tree} 32. Kg2
$18) 32. Ra1 (32. Bd7 {might be the shorter path} a6 $18) 32... h5 (32... Rf8 {
is not the saving move} 33. a5 $18) 33. Ba3 Nc8 (33... Bxa3 {desperation} 34.
Rxa3 a6 $18) 34. Bxd6 Nxd6 35. Rc1 Kh6 (35... Kg8 {does not save the day} 36.
Rc7 Rh6 37. Rd7 Nxb5 38. Rxb7 $18) 36. Rc7 h4 (36... Bc8 {a fruitless try to
alter the course of the game} 37. Rxa7 Rf8 38. Rc7 $18) 37. Rd7 Nxb5 38. Rxb7 (
38. axb5 $142 {makes sure everything is clear} Bc8 39. Rd8 a6 40. Rxc8 axb5 41.
gxh4 Kg7 $18) 38... Nd6 39. Rxa7 Ne4 (39... h3 {does not help much} 40. Rc7 $18
) 40. Rb7 hxg3 (40... Rf8 {does not improve anything} 41. Rxb6 Rc8 42. Nc6 $18)
41. Nxg3 Rf8 (41... Nf2+ {doesn't change anything anymore} 42. Kg2 Nh3 43. Ne2
$18) 42. Rxb6 Rh8 (42... Kg7 {praying for a miracle} 43. a5 Rc8 44. Nxe4 Rc1+
45. Kg2 dxe4 $18) 43. Nf7+ (43. Nf7+ Kh7 44. Nxh8 $18) (43. Nxf5+ Kh7 44. Rb7+
Kg8 45. Rg7+ Kf8 46. Rf7+ Ke8 47. Ng7+ Kd8 48. Nc6+ Kc8 49. Nxe6 Ng3+ 50. Kg2
Rxh2+ 51. Kxh2 Nf1+ 52. Kg1 Ne3 53. Rc7#) 1-0

